documentation.value: \brief This function is intended to set the Continuous or Mono conversion mode in the selected temperature sensor. By default the function set the Mono mode This function make use of SPI transactions \details If the temperature sensor is working in Continuous conversion mode, the way to deactivate it is going back to Mono mode just after ADCOUT_VALID is HIGH to avoid an extra conversion. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where to set the Continuous or Mono mode \param [in] conversionMode variable indicating whether setting Continuous conversion mode or Mono conversion mode. \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to check whether a temperature conversion has been completed or not This function make usage of SPI transactions \details The function checks HW flags RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_STATUS_TEMPOUT_VALID_BIT or RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_STATUS_ADCOUT_VALID_BIT depending on selected temperature output format parameter. Notice that when using \attention When using RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_STATUS_ADCOUT_VALID_BIT, we can poll whether the conversion has happened earlier than when using RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_STATUS_TEMPOUT_VALID_BIT. Please refer to temperature datasheet Table 5. Resolution mode input,C028HPCP_TDC1DG10K, C028HPCP High Accuracy Temperature-to-Digital Converter Rev. 1.4, 14 October 2020. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where to read conversion completion \param [in] temperatureOutputFormat variable indicating temperature output format, converted temperature or raw ADC value \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return bool indicating whether the conversion has finished ( true ) or not ( false )

\brief This function is intended to retrieve the measured temperature from selected temperature sensor This function make usage of SPI transactions. \details The function will check whether the conversion has been completed prior to read the temperature. In case the conversion isn't completed, the function will throw the error rfe_error_tSenseConversionInProgress_e being returned temperature set to 0x0ul, hence the caller has to ensure calling the function after conversion time has been completed. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where to read temperature conversion \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return rfe_temperature_t containing temperature in Celsius provided by temperature sensor using SQ6 fixed point notation. The resolution of returned temperature for this encoding is then 1/2^(6) = 0.01562 C

\brief This function is intended to calculate the equivalent temperature from the raw ADC output after a conversion based on configured fitting parameters A,B, Alpha and Xoffset in the selected temperature sensor This function make use of SPI transactions \details The function performs the calculation of the temperature based on section 10.3 Trimming Equations of temperature sensor documentation C028HPCP_TDC1DG10K, C028HPCP High Accuracy Temperature-to-Digital Converter Rev. 1.4, 14 October 2020. Being the equations \f$ xout = \frac{N{adc}}{adcOut}\f$ \f$ T_{trim} = A * \frac{Alpha}{Alpha + xout - X_{offset}} + B \f$. The equation is implemented in floating point and the result is casted into an rfe_temperature_t using Q6 fixed point format \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where to read raw ADC value to obtain its temperature \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return rfe_temperature_t result of converting the raw ADC value into its equivalent temperature. Notice that this output is in Q6 fixed point format.

\brief This function is intended to set the under-temperature and over-tempreature thresholds of the selected temperature sensor. This function make usage of SPI transactions \details The function checks the validity of the thresholds to be set, if the intended values to set are not within the allowed range, defined by RFE_HW_TSENSE_MINIMUM_SUPPORTED_TEMPERATURE_Q6 <= tresholdValue <= RFE_HW_TSENSE_MAXIMUM_SUPPORTED_TEMPERATURE_Q6, the function will throw an error. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where thresholds will be set \param [in] lowerTempThreshold under-temperature threshold value to be set in degree Celsius \param [in] higherTempTrehshold over-temperature threshold value to be set in degree Celsius \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to set the temperature warning sensor in the selected temperature sensor This function make usage of SPI transactions \details The function checks the validity of the thresholds to be set, if the intended values to set are not within the allowed range, defined by RFE_HW_TSENSE_MINIMUM_SUPPORTED_TEMPERATURE_Q6 <= warningTempThreshold <= RFE_HW_TSENSE_MAXIMUM_SUPPORTED_TEMPERATURE_Q6, the function will throw an error. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where threshold will be set \param [in] warningTempThreshold threshold value for the warning to be set in degree Celsius \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief This function is intended to set the temperature hysteresis threshold on the selected temperature sensor This function make usage of SPI transactions \details The function checks the validity of the thresholds to be set, if the intended values to set are not within the allowed range, defined by RFE_HW_TSENSE_MINIMUM_SUPPORTED_TEMPERATURE_Q6 <= hystThreshold <= RFE_HW_TSENSE_MAXIMUM_SUPPORTED_TEMPERATURE_Q6, the function will throw an error. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where threshold will be set \param [in] hystThreshold threshold value for the hysteresis to be set in degree Celsius \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

documentation.value: \brief This function is intended to trigger a temperature measurement for the selected temperature sensor This function make usage of 2SPI transactions \details Notice that in Mono mode the HW will reset the associated bit which controls starting temperature conversions every time that a conversion has taken place. Conversely, for Continuous mode HW does not reset this associated bit; therefore, if the Continuous mode wants to be disabled this function has to be called with enableConversion set to false. This ensures that last temperature conversion finishes properly before disabling further conversions. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where to start a temperature measurement \param [in] enableConversion boolean indicating whether to enable a conversion ( true ) or not ( false ). \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER

\brief Modifies an offline SPI register value. \details An offline SPI register consists on a register value which has been read out by another SPI function, and whose content/bits need to be modify without calling a SPI functionality. For example regValue will become an offline SPI register, since we read it first and the we want to extract certain bits from it. 1. We read regValue as below rfeHwSpi_register32_t regValue = rfeHwSpi_read( rfeHwTsense_indexMapperToSPIModule( tSenseIndex, RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_ARGUMENT ), RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_OUT0_REG, RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_ARGUMENT ); 2. Now we want to get certain bits from regValue without modify them on-the-fly via SPI, so we use this function to extract them readTemperature = rfeHwTsense_unpackBitsViaMask( regValue, RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_OUT0_TEMPOUT_MSK, RFE_HW_TSENSE_TDC_OUT0_TEMPOUT_SHF ); \param reg The offline SPI register value. \param mask Mask indicating which bits should be replaced in the offline SPI register value with the bits in value. \param shiftToApply Bit shift value needed to apply \return rfe_temperature_t Unpacked bits selected via mask and shift as signed rfe_temperature_t

\brief Function that maps the tSenseIndex for the four temperature sensor with its SPI module address so that the API may make use of this function This function doesn't make any SPI transaction \details The temperature sensor mapping can be seen in rfe_types.h and it is as follows RFE_HW_SPI_TEMP_1_MODULE -> The temperature sensor located near the receiver. RFE_HW_SPI_TEMP_2_MODULE -> The temperature sensor located near transmitter 1 and 2. RFE_HW_SPI_TEMP_3_MODULE -> The temperature sensor located near transmitter 3 and 4. RFE_HW_SPI_TEMP_4_MODULE -> The temperature sensor located near the XO. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature index to be mapped into its SPI module address counterpart \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return rfeHwSpi_module_t SPI module address counterpart for the tSenseIndex selected

\brief This function is intended to retrieve the converted raw ADC value for temperature from selected temperature sensor This function make use of SPI transactions. \details The function will check whether the conversion has been completed prior to read the raw ADC. In case the conversion isn't completed, the function will throw the error rfe_error_tSenseConversionInProgress_e being returned raw ADC value set to 0x0ul, hence the caller has to ensure calling the function after conversion time has been completed. \param [in] tSenseIndex temperature sensor where to read raw ADC conversion value \param [in/out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER \return rfeHwTsense_fixedPointQ15_t containing raw ADC register value which uses Q15 fixed point format
